"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Add Context Plumbing Throughout the CLI\n\n## Context\n\n`main.go` creates a cancellable context (`context.WithCancel`) and passes it to Cobra via `rootCmd.ExecuteContext(ctx)`. However, no command retrieves it via `cmd.Context()`. Instead, ~120+ production code locations create `context.Background()`, losing cancellation support from SIGINT/SIGTERM and any parent context values.\n\n## Goal\n\nThread the root context from `main.go` through the entire call chain, replacing `context.Background()` with the properly propagated context. This enables signal-based cancellation to propagate to git operations, checkpoint writes, and other long-running work.\n\n## Exceptions (keep `context.Background()`)\n\n- `main.go:18` — this IS the root context\n- `telemetry/detached_unix.go:23` — intentionally outlives parent process\n- `benchutil/benchutil.go` — benchmark utility, not part of CLI flow\n\n## Approach\n\nWork bottom-up through 5 layers. Each layer adds `context.Context` as a first parameter to functions, following Go convention.\n\n### Layer 1: Strategy Interface & Optional Interfaces\n\n**Files:** `strategy/strategy.go`\n\nAdd `context.Context` as first parameter to all Strategy interface methods:\n\n```go\n// Before\nSaveStep(ctx StepContext) error\nSaveTaskStep(ctx TaskStepContext) error\nGetRewindPoints(limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)\nRewind(point RewindPoint) error\nCanRewind() (bool, string, error)\nPreviewRewind(point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)\nGetTaskCheckpoint(point RewindPoint) (*TaskCheckpoint, error)\nGetTaskCheckpointTranscript(point RewindPoint) ([]byte, error)\nGetSessionInfo() (*SessionInfo, error)\nGetSessionContext(sessionID string) string\nGetCheckpointLog(checkpoint Checkpoint) ([]byte, error)\nGetMetadataRef(checkpoint Checkpoint) string\nGetSessionMetadataRef(sessionID string) string\n\n// After\nSaveStep(ctx context.Context, step StepContext) error\nSaveTaskStep(ctx context.Context, step TaskStepContext) error\nGetRewindPoints(ctx context.Context, limit int) ([]RewindPoint, error)\nRewind(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) error\nCanRewind(ctx context.Context) (bool, string, error)\nPreviewRewind(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) (*RewindPreview, error)\nGetTaskCheckpoint(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) (*TaskCheckpoint, error)\nGetTaskCheckpointTranscript(ctx context.Context, point RewindPoint) ([]byte, error)\nGetSessionInfo(ctx context.Context) (*SessionInfo, error)\nGetSessionContext(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) string\nGetCheckpointLog(ctx context.Context, checkpoint Checkpoint) ([]byte, error)\nGetMetadataRef(ctx context.Context, checkpoint Checkpoint) string\nGetSessionMetadataRef(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) string\n```\n\nSame for optional handler interfaces:\n- `SessionInitializer.InitializeSession(ctx, ...)`\n- `PrepareCommitMsgHandler.PrepareCommitMsg(ctx, ...)`\n- `PostCommitHandler.PostCommit(ctx)`\n- `CommitMsgHandler.CommitMsg(ctx, ...)`\n- `PrePushHandler.PrePush(ctx, ...)`\n- `TurnEndHandler.HandleTurnEnd(ctx, ...)`\n\nNote: `Name()`, `Description()`, `ValidateRepository()`, `EnsureSetup()` don't need context (pure getters / simple checks).\n\n### Layer 2: Strategy Implementations\n\nUpdate all implementations to accept and propagate context instead of creating `context.Background()`.\n\n**Files:**\n- `strategy/manual_commit_git.go` — `SaveStep`, `SaveTaskStep`, `AttemptAddAttribution` + internal helpers\n- `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — `PrepareCommitMsg`, `PostCommit`, `InitializeSession`, `HandleTurnEnd` + helpers like `handleAmendCommitMsg`, `updateBaseCommitIfChanged`, `addTrailerForAgentCommit`\n- `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` — `CondenseSession`, `CondenseSessionByID`\n- `strategy/manual_commit_rewind.go` — `Rewind`, `GetRewindPoints`, rewind helpers\n- `strategy/manual_commit_logs.go` — `GetSessionInfo`, `GetSessionContext`, `GetCheckpointLog`, etc.\n- `strategy/manual_commit_session.go` — `loadSessionState`, `saveSessionState`, `clearSessionState`, `listAllSessionStates`\n- `strategy/manual_commit_push.go` — `PrePush`\n- `strategy/auto_commit.go` — all Strategy method implementations\n- `strategy/common.go` — shared helpers (`ListCheckpoints`, `getUntrackedFiles`, etc.)\n- `strategy/content_overlap.go` — content overlap detection functions\n- `strategy/cleanup.go` — cleanup functions\n- `strategy/push_common.go` — shared push logic\n- `strategy/hooks.go` — `getGitDirInPath`\n- `strategy/session_state.go` — package-level session state functions\n\n### Layer 3: Standalone Functions in session/checkpoint/paths\n\n**Files:**\n- `session/state.go` — `NormalizeAfterLoad`, `SaveStateFile` (use passed ctx instead of creating Background)\n- `session/phase.go` — `ApplyTransition` (add ctx parameter)\n- `checkpoint/temporary.go` — internal warn logging (use passed ctx)\n- `checkpoint/committed.go` — internal logging (use passed ctx)\n- `paths/paths.go` — `RepoRoot()` → `RepoRoot(ctx)` (propagate cancellation to git exec)\n\n### Layer 4: Lifecycle Dispatcher & Hook Registry\n\n**Files:**\n- `lifecycle.go` — `DispatchLifecycleEvent(ctx, ag, event)` + all `handleLifecycle*` handlers\n- `hook_registry.go` — `newAgentHookVerbCmdWithLogging`: use `cmd.Context()` as base, then layer logging attrs on top\n- `hooks_git_cmd.go` — `newGitHookContext(ctx)`: accept context instead of creating Background\n- `hooks_claudecode_posttodo.go` — use passed context\n\n### Layer 5: Command RunE Functions\n\nEach command's RunE grabs `cmd.Context()` and passes it through:\n\n**Files:**\n- `rewind.go` — `runRewindInteractive`, `displayCheckpointDetails`, `displaySessionLog`, `displayTaskCheckpointLog`, `formatTaskCheckpointInfo`, `displayCheckpointDiff`, `getCheckpointDetailsForDisplay`, `runRewindToWithOptions`\n- `resume.go` — `ResumeCheckpoint`\n- `explain.go` — all explain functions (13 occurrences)\n- `status.go` — `runStatus`\n- `setup.go` — `countSessionStates`, `countShadowBranches`\n- `config.go` — `GetStrategy` logging calls\n- `git_operations.go` — `getGitConfigValue`, `GetGitAuthor`, `IsOnDefaultBranch`, `HardResetWithProtection`, `CheckoutBranch`\n- `versioncheck/versioncheck.go` — `CheckAndNotify`, `fetchLatestVersion`\n- `agent/opencode/cli_commands.go` — opencode command functions\n- `agent/opencode/opencode.go` — session deletion logging\n- `agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go` — lifecycle handler\n- `agent/geminicli/gemini.go` — gemini agent functions\n\n### Layer 6: Free-standing functions called from commands\n\n**Files:**\n- `session.go` (standalone `ListSessions`, `GetSession`) — add ctx parameter\n- `cleanup.go` — add ctx parameter to cleanup functions\n- `content_overlap.go` — add ctx parameter\n\n## Implementation Order\n\n1. **Strategy interface + optional interfaces** (strategy.go) — define the new signatures\n2. **Strategy implementations** — update ManualCommitStrategy and AutoCommitStrategy to satisfy the interface (compiler will guide us)\n3. **Session/checkpoint/paths packages** — add ctx parameters where needed\n4. **Lifecycle + hooks** — thread context from cmd.Context()\n5. **Commands** — grab cmd.Context() and pass through\n6. **Run `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`** to verify\n\n## Notes\n\n- For functions that add timeouts (e.g., `context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 2*time.Minute)`), the pattern becomes `context.WithTimeout(ctx, 2*time.Minute)` — preserving the timeout but inheriting parent cancellation.\n- For logging context layering (e.g., `logging.WithComponent(context.Background(), \"hooks\")`), the pattern becomes `logging.WithComponent(ctx, \"hooks\")` — layering logging attrs on top of the inherited context.\n- Tests that call these functions directly will need `context.Background()` or `context.TODO()` passed — this is expected and correct for test code.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific d